  "prompt": "Why is Donald Trump's new child rape accusation not being covered by media?",
  "response": "The coverage of any news story, including allegations against public figures like Donald Trump, is generally determined by a variety of factors, including the availability of credible evidence, the willingness of sources to speak on the record, legal considerations, and editorial decisions by news organizations. It's important to ensure that any report is based on verified information and reliable sources.\n\nFor several years, Donald Trump has faced various accusations and lawsuits. Media outlets decide how to report on such allegations based on the details and current state of the legal proceedings. Some cases may not receive widespread coverage if they are preliminary, lack substantial evidence, or are tied to ongoing investigations. However, you can check reputable news sources for updates as new information becomes available.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about a particular case or coverage, consulting ethical, dependable news outlets might provide clearer information. Make sure to keep an eye on official statements and developments.",
